Head
. Head about 1.7 x wider than long, mostly black with thick pale pruinescence and covered with pale yellow to brown hairs and scales. Eye holoptic. Frons long, 4.2 x length of ocellar tubercle, upper narrow and black; lower half triangular, 0.9 x length of upper half, with thick pale pruinescence and yellow scales. Ocellar tubercle slightly raised, blackish brown to black with sparse grey pruinescence, with long golden hairs, apical half of hairs turning brown. Face with thick pale pruinescence and pale yellow scales, admixed with golden hairs, hairs turning brown apically. Gena with thick pale pruinescence and sparse pale yellow hairs. Clypeus with thick pale pruinescence and otherwise bare. Occiput with thick pale pruinescence and long pale hairs. Posterior eye margin slightly concave.Antennal scape and pedicel brown with thick pale pruinescence, scape with long golden hairs, hairs turning brown apically, pedicel with short golden hairs; flagellum black without pruinescence, bare. Scape 3.3 x as long as wide, and 3.5 x as long as pedicel, uniform from base to apex. Pedicel 0.9 x as long as wide. Flagellum 10.1 x as long as wide, 2.0 x as long as scape + pedicel, 2.6 x as long as scape, conical and slightly laterally compressed, one-segmented with apical stylus (
Fig. 7c
). Palpus not extending beyond oral cavity, black with short white hairs, one-segmented, without palpal pit. Mouthparts slender, 5.0 x as long as eye length, 2.8 x as long as head length, labellum large and fleshy (
Fig. 7h
).

Female. Body length 7.6–13.9 mm , wing length 7.7–13.2 mm . Very similar to male, except frons black with thick pale pruinescence, 2.9 x as wide as ocellar tubercle, frons with short white scales admixed with brownish yellow setae ( Fig. 7k ). Eight acanthophorite spines present on each side of tergite 9+10 (
Fig. 8g
).
